#### Step 3
Add a event handler to the login button to check if successfully login(in this case we use whether the token in the action response is not null to check it).  

If successfully login, 1. use the token to set globalData 2. show a notification 3. setRouter(which means change page) to homepage View 1

```
const login_token = await login_api.trigger();
if(login_token.token!=""&&login_token.token!=undefined){
utils.setGlobalDataValue({key:"token",value:login_token.token});
  utils.showNotification({type:"info",title:"Successfully login",description:"current user: "+login_token.firstName+" "+login_token.lastName,duration:4500});
utils.setRouter({pagePath:"homepage",viewPath:"View 1"});
}else{
utils.showNotification({type:"info",title:"Failed to login",description:"",duration:4500});
};
```

